The Herald Tadious Manyepo Sports Reporter BLACK Rhinos legend Gift “Guava” Kamuriwo has died. He was 46. Kamuriwo, who also played for the Warriors in the early 2000s passed on at a military hospital this morning. Former Rhinos organising secretary Wellington Mabiginye who served during the same time Kamuriwo was the team manager confirmed the sad development. “It’s sad l have received word that Gift” Guava Kamuriwo” has died. “He has been unwell for some time,” he said.